<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1081,1179]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
Eighteen species of this genus occur in the Palaearctic Region, mainly in the Mediterranean (
<bibRefCitation author="Pagliano, G. &amp; Brothers, D. J. &amp; Cambra, R. &amp; Lelej, A. S. &amp; Lo Cascio, P. &amp; Matteini Palmerini, M. &amp; Scaramozzino, P. L. &amp; Williams, K. A. &amp; Romano, M." box="[1200,1429,1081,1107]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" pagination="5 - 425" refId="ref19407" refString="Pagliano, G., Brothers, D. J., Cambra, R., Lelej, A. S., Lo Cascio, P., Matteini Palmerini, M., Scaramozzino, P. L., Williams, K. A. &amp; Romano, M. (2020 [&quot; 2018 &quot;]) Checklist of names in Mutillidae (Hymenoptera), with illustrations of selected species. Bollettino del Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali di Torino, 36 (1 - 2), 5 - 425." type="journal article" year="2020">
Pagliano 
<emphasis box="[1307,1364,1081,1107]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
) and one species in Oriental Region (
<bibRefCitation author="Williams, K. A. &amp; Lelej, A. S. &amp; Okayasu, J. &amp; Borkent, C. J. &amp; Malee, R. &amp; Thoawan, K. &amp; Thaochan, N." box="[563,800,1117,1143]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 69" refId="ref20669" refString="Williams, K. A., Lelej, A. S., Okayasu, J., Borkent, C. J., Malee, R., Thoawan, K. &amp; Thaochan, N. (2019) The female velvet ants (aka modkhong) of southern Thailand (Hymenoptera: Mutillidae), with a key to the genera of southeast Asia. Zootaxa, 4602 (1), 1 - 69. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4602.1.1" type="journal article" year="2019">
Williams 
<emphasis box="[674,732,1117,1143]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
). Only one species of this genus has been reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,278,1153,1179]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
